## Prebuilt binaries

Every [release](<< .GitHubURL >>/releases) carries archives for Linux, macOS,
and Windows on amd64 and arm64, plus deb, rpm, and apk packages for Linux.
Download, unpack, put `<< .Binary >>` on your `PATH`, done. The `checksums.txt`
on each release is signed with keyless [cosign](https://docs.sigstore.dev/) if
you want to verify before running.

## With Go

```bash
go install << .Module >>/cmd/<< .Binary >>@latest
```

That puts `<< .Binary >>` in `$(go env GOPATH)/bin`, which is `~/go/bin` unless
you moved it. Make sure that directory is on your `PATH`.

## From source

```bash
git clone << .GitHubURL >>
cd << .Repo >>
make build        # produces ./bin/<< .Binary >>
./bin/<< .Binary >> version
```

## Container image

```bash
docker run --rm << .Image >>:latest --help
```

## Checking the install

```bash
<< .Binary >> version
```

prints the version and exits.
